<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM22020 - Eligibility &amp; Material Interest: Time of eligibility to participate</h1>
<p>The rules of a SIP must provide that an employee may participate in an award under the plan only if he or she is eligible to do so at the appropriate time.  In the case of free shares, the employee must be eligible to participate at the time of the award of free shares (paragraph 14(2)). </p>
<p>In the case of partnership and matching shares, the employee must be eligible either:</p>
<ul>
<li>at the time the partnership share money is deducted from salary (pay day), where there is no accumulation period (paragraph 14(3)) or </li>
<li>at the time of the first salary deduction (pay day), where there is an accumulation period (paragraph 14(4)).</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that an employee who ceases to satisfy one or more of the eligibility requirements after the appropriate time but nevertheless remains in relevant employment will be entitled to participate in the award of partnership shares.  If there is an accumulation period and the employee transfers from a constituent company (see <a href="ESSUM28250.htm">ESSUM28250</a>) to another associated company (see <a href="ESSUM29350.htm">ESSUM29350</a>) which is not a constituent company, deductions of partnership share money must stop.  Partnership shares will be acquired in due course using partnership share money accumulated up to the transfer of employment.</p>
<p>An employee is “eligible to participate” only if he or she meets the following plan requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li>employment: (see <a href="ESSUM22100.htm">ESSUM22100</a>)</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li class="blockquote2">
<ul>
<li>with the establishing company  or</li>
<li>in the case of a group plan, a constituent company (paragraph 15) (see <a href="ESSUM28350).htm">ESSUM28350)</a>;</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>not participating simultaneously in connected SIPs (paragraph 18); (see <a href="ESSUM22300.htm">ESSUM22300</a>)</li>
<li>successive participation in connected SIPs (paragraph 18A); (see <a href="ESSUM22350.htm">ESSUM22350</a>) and</li>
<li>material interest (paragraph 19) (see <a href="ESSUM22400.htm">ESSUM22400</a>).</li>
</ul>
<p>The employee may also be required to satisfy certain authorised conditions - in the case of free shares, for example, performance allowances may need to be achieved (see <a href="ESSUM24140.htm">ESSUM24140</a>).</p>
